  "prompt": "Are there any gurus currently in the marketing industry who are saying something really new about the future of communication planning?",
  "response": "While I don't have real-time information about the absolute latest marketing insights, some prominent thought leaders who are discussing innovative communication planning approaches include:\n\n1. Gary Vaynerchuk\n- Emphasizes authentic, platform-specific content\n- Focuses on micro-content and understanding emerging social media platforms\n\n2. Seth Godin\n- Discusses \"permission marketing\"\n- Advocates for storytelling and creating remarkable content\n\n3. Mark Schaefer\n- Explores \"content shock\" and sustainable content marketing strategies\n- Writes about human-centered marketing approaches\n\n4. Brian Solis\n- Studies digital transformation\n- Analyzes how technology changes communication and consumer behaviors\n\n5. Ann Handley\n- Promotes conversational, human-centered content marketing\n- Emphasizes quality storytelling over volume\n\nEmerging themes they're discussing include:\n- AI-enhanced personalization\n- More authentic, less polished communication\n- Integration of short-form video content\n- Decentralized marketing through creator economies\n- Increased emphasis on purpose-driven brand communication\n\nWhile these perspectives are interesting, the most innovative ideas are constantly evolving. I'd recommend following their current publications and conference presentations for the most up-to-date insights.\n\nWould you like me to elaborate on any of these perspectives?",
